Q.7 Clone Git Project Using Jenkins Webhook

Step 1:
Enable Trigger
Build Triggers →
GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling

Step 2:
Install ngrok
sudo dpkg -i ngrok-v3-stable-linux-amd64.deb

Step 3:
Add ngrok Token
ngrok config add-authtoken YOUR_TOKEN

Step 4:
Start ngrok
ngrok http 8080

Copy URL:
https://scale-faceplate-hypnotize.ngrok-free.dev/

Step 5:
Configure Jenkins URL
Manage Jenkins → System

Jenkins URL:
https://scale-faceplate-hypnotize.ngrok-free.dev/

Step 6:
Add GitHub Webhook
Repo → Settings → Webhooks

Payload URL:
https://scale-faceplate-hypnotize.ngrok-free.dev/github-webhook/

Content Type:
application/json

Event:
Just the push event

Step 7:
Test Webhook
git add .
git commit -m "Webhook Test"
git push

Step 8:
Verify Build

Started by GitHub push

Jenkins automatically fetch latest code:
git fetch --tags --force --progress -- https://github.com/PriyanshuSingh21july2021/Java-code.
